value.0: Yer back! Did ye deliver the letter?
Wut?? Ye lost me letter! Oh an' I suppose I'm meant ta believe ye lost the coin tha was in there, too?? Yer either an idiot, o' a thief! Go on, get tae feck outta here!
Bull-shite, ah say! Yer a damned thief, or an' idiot! Go on , get tae feck outta here!
Yer back! Did ye deliver the letter?
Yer back! Did ye deliver the letter?
Yer lyin', ye opened it an took the coin din't ye! Lyin' bastid, get tae fuck!
An did ye open it afore ye gave it te her?
Ye git, ye took the coin didn't ye? Did ye even deliv'r tha letter? Damn yer eyes, ye bastid! Git outta here afore ma mates beat tha shit outta ye!
Hmm... aright, ah believe ya
Wut?? Ye lost me letter! Oh an' I suppose I'm meant ta believe ye lost the coin tha was in there, too?? Yer either an idiot, o' a thief! Go on, get tae feck outta here!
An did ye open it afore ye gave it te her?
Yer lyin', ah don't care if ye delivered it OR the coin, yer not gettin anythin' from me. Now git tae fuck!
Ha! Ye think ye can scare me, look around. These big'uns is all me mates. Jus' try an threaten me agin, eh? We'll see who's the scary one then.
Aright, aright! Fer feck's sake. Take the coin an git.
Nae I said, git out this place an' don't come back!
Hmm... *glares at you* well, ah s'pose so.. here, 'ave yer pay. But don't come snoopin' round 'ere agin, ye here!
Hmm... aright, ah believe ya
Ye read ma private letter what wis entrusted tae yer safe keepin? Feck off, ye creepy bastid! No pay fer a snoop!
Yer lyin', ye opened it an took the coin din't ye! Lyin' bastid, get tae fuck!
Hmm... aright, ah believe ya
*angrily* what da ye wan'? Clear off, ye hear?
*angrily* ye didnae have tae tell Keegan! Am gon' get a beatin' like ye wouldnae believe! An poor Doris is out there on 'er own now, 'avin me child... Yer a bastid, well an true. Git tae fuck!
'am in yer debt, friend. Thanks agin.
Yer back! Did ye deliver the letter?

*sighs heavily* ah well... this'll be wha' happens when ye go sowin wild oats, as me mother used tae say. Come tae think o' it, me mother still says tha', every time ah see her! As if a' need remindin'!

Here's yer payment. Ye earned it.
Wha', really?? Well ain't ye a blessin o' the Mother her'sel! Thanks, frien'!
Ye need tae hurry... there's a time limit 'o sorts on how useful tha' letter gonna be tae her... git on wae it!
Mm? *looks up at you, distracted* Eh? What 're you doin' in here?

Gah! Wurried?! 'am a Guardsman of this here Caer! Ah don't get wurried.

...although, come to think of it, ye might be able tae help me out wit' somethin.

This 'ere letter. There's a lass in the city I need it deliverin' to, an SOON, it's VERY impor'ant, ye see? 

An I need it done QUIET-like. High Constable Keegan's comin' tae inspect the barracks, an last time he caught me wit' contraband mail, 'e said he'd whip me if 'e caught me agin. Somethin' about 'focussing yer mind' or other daft shite. *spits* Gobshite.

Yer damned right it's importan'! An' urgent! Ye'll find 'er in the east o' the city. No doubt she's a-wanderin the street, wailin cus she en't received the... uh... uh... letter that ah promised 'er. 

She's a real beauty. Bright red hair, ye can't miss 'er. Name's Doris, so it is. Tell 'er this is from 'er Elsworth, got it?

An' remember, if'n ye're stoppin by the Caer for some reaon, don't be lettin' on tae High Constable Keegan! We don' call 'im Stick-up-his-arse Keegan fer nothin', ye get it?

...an one last thing! Dinnae be openin' ma letter, ya hear!
*his face colours a bit* ah, she may 'ave reason to be a tad upset, ye know.. *coughs awkwardly* just.. make sure it gets tae her, aright? An remember, don't ye let Constable Keegan find out!
Ah've a few crowns tucked away ah can give yer. An' ye'll have me thanks!
Suit yersel' *looks down miserably at the letter in his hands*
'old on a sec there.. you from the city, eh?
I, uh... 'lost' it
[PERSUADE] Actually, I gave Doris the 20 crowns that was in the letter. Sorry about losing it.
[BLUFF] I did!
What's it to you?
[BLUFF] No, of course not!
I, uh... 'lost' it
Whatever. I'm leaving.
I did!
[BLUFF] No, of course not!
[INTIMIDATE] You promised me coin. I ran your errand. Cough up, or I'll tell your Constable you've been sneaking to the city at night and knocked up a girl.
[PERSUADE] All right all right, I read it... what's the harm? At least I delivered it - AND the coin too.
Yes I did, but I delivered it anyway, and the coin in it too.
Fine, whatever *leave without being paid*
[BLUFF] No, of course not!
..well?? Where's my reward!
I did. Doris seemed... very relieved. She said to thank you and not to worry, that the money 'would be enough'. What was that all about?
Thanks. Try not to catch any diseases.
Actually, no need for payment, friend. Just happy to help you out in a difficult situation.
No problem.
Not yet.
Just looking around. Why do you look so worried?
Nuh-uh, I can see where this is going. Not interested.
I didn't come snooping around your bunk bed looking to do you a favour. What would be in it for me?
*sigh* oh yes, I see... what is it then?
Fine. I'll help you with this extremely important mission.
Wailing in the streets?! You must be joking.
Whatever. Give me the letter.
What's in it for me?
A paltry fee and 'thanks'?! Sod off.
Oh, uh... sorry. Didn't mean to disturb your thoughts. I'll be going!
None of your business. Good day, sir!
I am passing through. Why do you look so worried?
